The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for subcortical brain structure segmentation in MRI. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for this task, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the use of GPUs for efficient training, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large-scale datasets, which is a topic of interest in multimedia (cs.MM).
